PR-_____ | International | Cultural Alignment/Reconciliation | Clearly defining problems relies on being able to define what a problem is. What is a problem for some is often a problem for others, but could sometimes be a benefit for others. In order to reach such a definition, often this means values alignment must take place. A body of people of diverse backgrounds do not always agree which parts of status quo need changing nor do they always share an understanding of the consequncess of any proposed change.
PR-_____ | International | Lack of Global Shared Language (International Common Language) | To solve problems cross-culturally humanity needs to have a shared, fully expressive, and inclusive means of communications. Internet dialects combining English with a number of other commonly used Romantic and Slavic languages are beginning to fill this role, but without standardization and spread of such a common language, disconnected peoples will remain unable to communicate and participate in the conversations about the future of humanity happening online.
