PR-22917 | International | Deforestation of the Tropical Rain Forest | Earth is losing its tropical rain forests at an alarming rate, which will have a significant and likely negative impact on humanity which we do not yet fully understand.
PR-84721 | International (G20 Nations) | Social Tension From Wealth Inequality | As of 2021, the top 1% of US households hold 32% of the country's wealth, while the bottom 50% hold only 2%, exacerbating social tensions. Similar tensions are emerging in other highly developed nations such as Italy, France, United Kingdom, et al. 
PR-35698 | United States of America | MRSA Infections in US Hospitals | Methicillin-resistant Staphylococcus aureus (MRSA) causes over 323,000 hospitalizations and 10,600 deaths annually in the US, challenging traditional treatments.
PR-62103 | International | Microplastic Pollution in the Mediterranean Sea | The Mediterranean Sea contains 1.25 million metric tons of plastic, with microplastics affecting marine life and potentially entering the human food chain.
