PR-95302 | United States of America | Food Waste in US Restaurants | US restaurants generate 22 to 33 billion pounds of food waste annually, contributing to environmental issues and economic losses.
PR-_____ | International (G7 Nations) | Native Depopulation and Declining Birthrates | According to PennWharton at The University of Pennsylvania, recent declines in the total fertility rate have pushed it below the population replacement level of 2.1 percent per woman. Recent declines in the total fertility rate have pushed it below the population replacement level of 2.1 percent per woman. The Penn Wharton Budget Model (PWBM) microsimulation projects the TFR to remain below this level during the next few decades. This could result in higher worker-retiree ratios and labor shortages if the shortage is not covered by increased immigration.
PR-27836 | State of Japan (日本国) | Aging Population in Japan | Japan's population over 65 reached 28.7% in 2020, causing labor shortages and putting pressure on healthcare and pension systems.
PR-68147 | United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland | Teen Depression in the UK | One in six UK youth aged 6-16 had a probable mental disorder in 2021, with pandemic lockdowns exacerbating the issue.
PR-_____ | International | Teen Mental Health Decline, including Anxiety and Depression | According to the WHO, One in seven 10-19-year-olds experiences a mental disorder, accounting for 15% of the global burden of disease in this age group. Depression, anxiety and behavioural disorders are among the leading causes of illness and disability among adolescents. Suicide  is the third leading cause of death among those aged 15–29 years old. The consequences of failing to address adolescent mental health conditions extend to adulthood, impairing both physical and mental health and limiting opportunities to lead fulfilling lives as adults.
