PR-xxxxx | State of São Paulo, Brazil | Insufficient Mental Health Services and Resources | Despite a significant and growing demand for mental health care in São Paulo, historical underinvestment and service gaps have limited public access to proper treatment. The recent allocation of R$ 31.9 million by the Brazilian government aims to expand and improve these services, addressing issues such as overcrowded facilities, lack of specialized professionals, and long waiting lists for mental health care.
